{
  "stem": "10710.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then he took him and my father in the back yard and told them to lay down and shot them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SOBBING] My sister told me later my father's last words were [NON-ENGLISH] And my sister and his wife had to stay by the window and see how they're being shot.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Of course, we made the minyan in, in Rabka.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had another few people who said Kaddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were able to say-- I wasn't able to sit shiva because I had to go to work the next day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I was able-- I was able to say Kaddish for about six months, as long as we were in, in, in Rabka.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then, then I was-- I was left there already, just with my sister.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My sister was home by herself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she got sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they took her to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a day before-- a day before they, they took the people from Stary Sacz to, to the bigger town-- there was the [NON-ENGLISH] They let the whole camp to go home from Rabka to Stary Sacz.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I came to four empty walls.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[SOBBING] There was nobody home anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I slept by myself, and I took with me whatever I could, you know, from the stuff in the house, lady stuff, and I was able later to sell it to the Christians and, and help myself with food.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this was the last time the people saw their families.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They took us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They, they, they went with us to the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Can you imagine a wife and children saying goodbye to their husbands and they, they knew they wouldn't see them anymore?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the next day was the-- they took them all out to Nowy Sacz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "From there, they sent them to Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
